    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Architecture &amp; Internals</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">How EmulatR is built and how a cold boot actually runs. These pages are the operator lens; it presents enough detail to reason about the machine without reading the source. The register-level detail lives in the Appendices&apos; Architecture Deep-Dives.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">In this section</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="NotesBox" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Overview -- the fidelity standard, the goals, the execution model, and the device fabric.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Memory -- the GuestMemory physical store and the chipset arbiter.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Addressing -- EV6 translation and the SPAM translation buffers.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Firmware Decode &amp; Decompression -- how the SRM image unpacks at cold boot.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Execution Flight Plan -- the cold-boot sequence end to end.</li>
    </list>
